                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13638871" author="tmielke" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2013 07:59:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching slightly modified version of DebugBlueprintTest.java in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6305&quot; title=&quot;debugBefore() and debugAfter() not called if unit test extends CamelBlueprintTestSupport&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-6305&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-6305&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.diff that can serve as unit test for this bug.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13639032" author="njiang" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2013 13:16:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is caused by BlueprintCamelContext is started before the setUp() is called.&lt;br/&gt;
We need to introduce a mechanism to avoid staring the BlueprintCamelContext when loading the bundle.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13640308" author="njiang" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2013 10:05:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s hard to block the starting process of BlueprintCamelContext before the bundle is start, because CamelContext will be publish as OSGi service after the BlueprintCamelContext is started. And CamelBlueprintTestSupport is looking up the CamelContext from the OSGi service registry. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I finally find a way to fix this issue by just stop the CamelContext in the setUp method if we need the debug feature.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13643618" author="njiang" created="Sat, 27 Apr 2013 09:53:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch into trunk, camel-2.11.x and camel-2.10.x branches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
